Before this git commit runs, check for Prisma schema drift across packages.

IMPORTANT: If Bash or Read tools are unavailable in this context, immediately output: {"continue": true, "hookSpecificOutput": {"hookEventName": "PreToolUse", "additionalContext": "schema-sync-check: skipped (tools unavailable)"}}

Background: server/prisma/schema.prisma, web/prisma/schema.prisma, and telegram-bot/prisma/schema.prisma all point at the same shared PostgreSQL database. telegram-bot runs `prisma db push` automatically on every deploy using its own copy of the schema — if a shared model's fields are out of sync across these files, db push can drop columns another service depends on, or fail outright and take down the bot.

1. Run: git diff --cached --name-only
   If none of server/prisma/schema.prisma, web/prisma/schema.prisma, telegram-bot/prisma/schema.prisma appear in the list — output ONLY: {"continue": true, "hookSpecificOutput": {"hookEventName": "PreToolUse", "additionalContext": "schema-sync-check: no prisma schema changes"}}

2. Otherwise, read the full current content (not just the diff) of all three files: server/prisma/schema.prisma, web/prisma/schema.prisma, telegram-bot/prisma/schema.prisma

3. Find every model name that appears in 2 or more of these files (shared models). For each shared model, compare its fields across the files it appears in:
   - Field present in one file's version of the model but missing in another → drift
   - Same field name but different type, nullability, @unique, or @default → drift
   - Ignore field order, comments, formatting

4. If any drift found on a model touched by this commit's diff (or any drift at all involving a model whose schema.prisma was just staged) — output ONLY: {"continue": false, "stopReason": "schema-sync-check blocked commit:\n<for each drift: Model.field present in X, missing/different in Y>\nFix: add the missing field(s) to the lagging schema file(s) so all packages sharing the DB stay in sync. Never use --accept-data-loss as a fix."}

5. If no drift — output ONLY: {"continue": true, "hookSpecificOutput": {"hookEventName": "PreToolUse", "additionalContext": "schema-sync-check: shared Prisma models are in sync across server/web/telegram-bot"}}

