Before this PR is created, run a security audit of the changes.

IMPORTANT: If Bash or Read tools are unavailable in this context, immediately output: {"continue": true, "hookSpecificOutput": {"hookEventName": "PreToolUse", "additionalContext": "security-reviewer: skipped (tools unavailable)"}}

Follow the instructions in .claude/agents/security-reviewer.md exactly.

Steps:
1. Run: git diff main...HEAD --name-only
2. If no security-relevant files changed (only UI, CSS, tests, config) — output ONLY: {"continue": true, "hookSpecificOutput": {"hookEventName": "PreToolUse", "additionalContext": "security-reviewer: no security-relevant files changed"}}
3. Otherwise read changed files in: server/src/routes/, server/src/middleware/, server/src/lib/auth.ts
4. Run npm audit only if package.json or package-lock.json changed
5. Apply the checklist from the agent file
6. CRITICAL issues — output ONLY: {"continue": false, "stopReason": "security-reviewer blocked PR:\n<issue>"}
7. Warnings — output ONLY: {"continue": true, "hookSpecificOutput": {"hookEventName": "PreToolUse", "additionalContext": "security-reviewer warnings:\n<list>"}}
8. Clean — output ONLY: {"continue": true, "hookSpecificOutput": {"hookEventName": "PreToolUse", "additionalContext": "security-reviewer: no security issues found"}}
